import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Load US states shapefile
    us_states = gpd.read_file("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.geojson")

    # Count cities per state
    city_counts = data.groupby('state').size().reset_index(name='city_count')

    # Merge city counts with states shapefile
    us_states = us_states.merge(city_counts, left_on='name', right_on='state')

    # Create choropleth map
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 25))
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)
    us_states.plot(column='city_count', cmap='coolwarm', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8', legend=True, cax=cax)

    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities across states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_first_letter_counts = data['first_letter'].value_counts().reset_index()
    city_first_letter_counts.columns = ['first_letter', 'count']
    chart = sns.barplot(x='first_letter', y='count', data=city_first_letter_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities based on their first letter?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('First Letter')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Cities')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='vowel_count', bins=range(0, data['vowel_count'].max() + 1), color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities based on their vowel count?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Vowel Count')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Cities')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='lon', y='lat', hue='state', data=data, palette='viridis', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across cities?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.legend(title='State', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby(['state', 'first_letter']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    data_pivot = data_grouped.pivot_table(index='state', columns='first_letter', values='count', fill_value=0)
    data_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(15, 8))

    plt.title("What is the distribution of cities across states based on their first letter?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("State")
    plt.ylabel("Count of Cities")
    plt.legend(title="First Letter", loc="upper right")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
